	<h1> Emma Yates Bio</h1>
	<body>
		<p>Emma Yates is an Australian born, New York based designer who specializes in unconventional bridal wear. Born to parents who never legally married, but still experienced a chaotic divorce, Emma aims to discuss and redefine ideas around marriage in her work. She draws much of her inspiration from her childhood spent between Sydney and Australian outback. Emma is passionate about supporting Australian farmers and works directly with farmers in the Hilltops Region to source her raw materials, before processing them to create looks for the modern bride.</p>

		<p>Emma has worked alongside a number of industry leaders including receiving sponsorships from Swarovski and Sophie Hallette for her Fall/Winter 2018 collection. </p>

		<p>In 2019 Emma was named as a finalist for the Parsons School of Fashion Luxarity Lane Crawford award.</p>

		<p>Work from By Emma Yates has been featured in several international publications including Fashionista, Huf Magazine, Ell√©ments Magazine and The Cootamundra Herald.</p>

		<p>Emma is completing her Bachelor of Fine Arts  at Parsons The New School for Design, majoring in Fashion design, and specializing in systems design and bridal design. She is also completing her Bachelor of Arts at Eugene Lang, The New School for Liberal Arts, majoring in media and communications for artists.</p>
	</body>
